ervision, the <strong>Maintenance Specialist I</strong> (MS I) performs minor routine maintenance and repair services on different types of vehicles. Works with the assistance of a MS II, MS III, MS IV, MS Lead, OS or OM, when performing technical and diagnostic type repairs. Task assignments are directed by operations management to encourage development in a productive manner. The MS I will support non-contractual Torque by Ryder customers. The mobile service truck, tools, and inventory must be maintained and kept in serviceable condition at all times as per company policy and procedures<br><br>The MS I will interact with relevant business support members and departments as needed. Task assignments are directed by direct supervisor, or by the scheduling call center. <br><br>This position is off-site and will not be assigned to a specific Torque by Ryder brick and mortar location, which will require extensive travel and exceptional customer focus. The MS I will represent Torque by Ryder and interact with non-contractual Ryder customers in order to establish a relationship and promote and develop business opportunities to up-sell Torque by Ryder's products and services. After the work shift has been completed, the MS I will take assigned mobile service truck home, but will be required to secure vehicle and contents as per company policy.<br><br>The MS I will be held to productivity standards unique to this role.<br><br>#INDTECH<br><br>#LI-Post<br><br>#FB<br><br>Requirements<ul><li>High school diploma or equivalent preferred</li><li>Basic tools, required </li><li>One (1) year or more experience in transportation maintenance, preferred</li><li>NonCommercial Driver License CLASS E, preferred</li><li>Valid Commercial Driver License (CDL) CLASS A, preferred</li><li>State driver's license, as required</li><li>Must have minimum tools required to perform their job duties as outlined in Ryder's Maintenance policy 2.02</li><li>Pass a Ryder drug test and previous employer's for